HEADWORD: Waxworker
<hw>Wax"work`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who works in wax; one who makes waxwork.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bee that makes or produces wax.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waxy</ent>⟦br⟧
